<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p>A <rs type="material">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">panel-stele</rs> (<measure dim="height" unit="metre" type="length">0.88</measure> x <measure dim="width" unit="metre" type="length">0.64</measure> x <measure dim="depth" unit="metre" type="length">0.21</measure>). The relief is of a nude facing <rs type="decoration">gladiator</rs>, who still wears arm-protectors on his right upper arm, and shin-guards. He holds a palm with his right arm, which is partly lost; his left arm is stretched out horizontally, and the hand rests on a helmet placed on what is either a smooth column or a tall shield. Below are two small figures: that on the man's right has shin-guards and a long shield, and looks up at him; that on his left is winged and naked, and holds his right arm down, and left arm raised, while regarding the central figure.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on upper (l.1) and lower (l.2) mouldings</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p>standard forms, <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.03</measure></p>
</div>
